SIMPLE: gouge
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gouge
<hw>Gouge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>gouge</ets>.
LL. <ets>gubia</ets>, <ets>guvia</ets>, <ets>gulbia</ets>,
<ets>gulvia</ets>, <ets>gulvium</ets>; cf. Bisc. <ets>gubia</ets> bow,
<ets>gubioa</ets> throat.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A chisel, with a hollow or semicylindrical blade,
for scooping or cutting holes, channels, or grooves, in wood, stone,
etc.; a similar instrument, with curved edge, for turning
wood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bookbinder's tool for blind tooling or gilding,
having a face which forms a curve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 641 --></p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An incising tool which cuts forms or blanks for
gloves, envelopes, etc. from leather, paper, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>Soft material lying between the
wall of a vein and the solid vein.</def> <rj><au>Raymond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>The act of scooping out with a gouge, or as with a
gouge; a groove or cavity scooped out, as with a gouge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Imposition; cheat; fraud; also, an impostor; a
cheat; a trickish person.</def> <mark>[Slang, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gouge bit</b></col>, <cd>a boring bit, shaped like a
gouge.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bouge</ent>⟦br⟧
